%% Data Flow Diagram - Workload Variant Autoscaler
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CMCtrl as ConfigMap Controller
    participant SatEngine as Saturation Engine
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant vLLM as vLLM Servers
    participant Cache as Decision Cache<br/>(in-memory)
    participant VACtrl as VariantAutoscaling<br/>Controller
    participant Actuator as WVA Actuator<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HPAKEDA as HPA / KEDA
    participant SFZ as Scale-from-Zero Engine
    participant EPP as EPP Metrics<br/>HTTPS TLS

    Note over Admin,EPP: Flow 1: Saturation-Based Autoscaling Decision

    SatEngine->>Prom: Query vLLM metrics<br/>Bearer Token (SA token)
    Prom->>vLLM: Scrape metrics<br/>(KV cache, queue depth)
    vLLM-->>Prom: Metrics response
    Prom-->>SatEngine: Metric values
    SatEngine->>Cache: Store scaling decisions
    Cache->>VACtrl: Read decisions (Go channel)
    VACtrl->>K8s: Update VariantAutoscaling status<br/>SA token
    SatEngine->>Actuator: Emit wva_desired_replicas,<br/>wva_desired_ratio
    HPAKEDA->>Actuator: GET /metrics<br/>Bearer Token, HTTPS/8443
    Actuator-->>HPAKEDA: wva_desired_ratio
    HPAKEDA->>K8s: Scale target (scale subresource)<br/>SA token

    Note over Admin,EPP: Flow 2: Scale-from-Zero

    SFZ->>EPP: Query flow control queue metrics<br/>Bearer Token (epp-metrics-token)
    EPP-->>SFZ: Queue metrics response
    SFZ->>K8s: Scale target from 0 to N<br/>(scale subresource, SA token)

    Note over Admin,EPP: Flow 3: Configuration Management

    Admin->>K8s: Create/Update ConfigMap<br/>User credentials
    K8s-->>CMCtrl: ConfigMap watch event<br/>SA token
    CMCtrl->>CMCtrl: Update in-memory config
